# Nix modules: flake-parts and explicit `config`

## Flake-parts (fp) modules

**Everything** in this repo that defines configuration should be a **flake-parts module**: a Nix file that `flake-parts` imports (e.g. under `modules/`, `users/`, `hosts/`) and that returns an attribute set of `flake`, `perSystem`, `options`, etc. Do not add ad-hoc `.nix` files that are never imported by the flake, or bypass the module system for “one-off” config. New features belong in a new (or existing) fp module that wires into `flake.*` or `perSystem` as the rest of the tree does.

## Inner modules: use `config` for settings

Leaf modules set `flake.{sharedModules,darwinModules,nixosModules,homeModules,nixvimModules}` (and `flake.userConfig.*.module` for Home Manager users). Those use **inner** NixOS-style module functions.

## Rule

In the **inner** module (the function body after `= { ... }:`), only these may appear at the top level next to each other:

- `imports`
- `options`
- `meta`
- `_module` (or other module-system escape hatches)

**All real configuration** (`programs`, `services`, `home`, `environment`, `users`, `nix`, `nixpkgs`, `home-manager`, nixvim `plugins` / `globals` / `keymaps` / `opts`, etc.) must live inside an explicit:

```nix
config = {
  # settings here
};
```

Use `config = lib.mkMerge [ ... ]` or `config = lib.mkIf cond { ... }` when you need merge or conditionals.

## Examples

```nix
# Good
{ ... }:
{
  flake.homeModules.example = { ... }: {
    imports = [ ./other.nix ];
    config = {
      programs.git.enable = true;
    };
  };
}

# Bad (shorthand config at top level)
{ ... }:
{
  flake.homeModules.example = { ... }: {
    imports = [ ./other.nix ];
    programs.git.enable = true;
  };
}
```

```nix
# Good (nixvim inner module)
{ ... }:
{
  flake.nixvimModules.plugins.foo = { ... }: {
    config = {
      plugins.foobar.enable = true;
    };
  };
}
```

**Outer** fp modules (only set `flake.*` or `perSystem`, no inner `= { ... }:`) are not “inner” modules. The `config` wrapper rule applies to **inner** submodule bodies (NixOS, Home Manager, nix-darwin, nixvim) that implement options and config.
